default one extra bedroom.
default 
defaultThis would br
defaulting the DWP definition close to 
defaultthe definition used by DCLG and the 
defaultsocial housing 
defaultsector for many years. It would help claimants living in social housing to thrive, supporting payment for modest additional space to allow separate bedrooms for teenage children to study, couples who face illness and disability and separated
default parents with access to children. It would reduce the numbers facin
defaultg reduced benefi
defaultt by 75%, and focus
default on dealing with ‘problematic’ levels of under-occupation. It would also give landlords the capacity to deal with the significant numbers of elderly tenan
defaultts (exempt from the penalty) who are under-occupying their homes and wish to move. A 
defaultrevised definition 
defaultwo
defaultuld 
defaultreduce the need to rely on inconsistently delivered discretionary assistance (DHP)
default, reduce the risk of tribunal challenge
